=============================================================================
Files added in this fork (not derived from upstream)
=============================================================================

Authored from scratch. Original work, Copyright (c) 2026 Tong Zhou,
released under the same MIT License as the rest of the repository.

- `LICENSE`, `NOTICE`, `README.md`, `README.zh-CN.md`
- `config.md` - sanitized template for personal config
  (API keys / email / institutional VPN hosts).
- `data/jcr.db` (~16 MB) - SQLite database of JCR metadata used by
  `scripts/journal_lookup.py`.
- `references/query-plan.md` - 4-phase structured query-plan schema and
  per-DB expression syntax cheat-sheet.
- `references/parallel.md` - rules for parallelising API-database calls
  (arXiv / S2 / PubMed) while keeping browser-driven databases
  (CNKI / WoS / GS) strictly serial.
- `references/cnki-advanced-search.md`,
  `references/cnki-delegation.md`,
  `references/cnki-download.md`
  - full CNKI (China National Knowledge Infrastructure) pipeline:
    expression-language spec, delegation contract, `dm8/API/GetExport`
    RIS export flow, and per-record PDF download UI sequence.
- `references/wos-delegation.md`, `references/wos-download.md` -
  Web of Science pipeline: institutional-VPN routing, advanced search,
  `Export -> Plain text` flow, Unpaywall-based open-access PDF lookup.
- `scripts/build_refs.py` (~664 lines) - cross-source RIS merger;
  reads `paper_raw/_tmp/{arxiv.xml, s2.json, pubmed.xml, cnki.ris,
  wos.txt, ...}`, cross-source dedupes (DOI > arXiv ID > WoS ID >
  title+year fuzzy), emits the final `paper_raw/refs.ris` + `summary.md`.
- `scripts/expand_queries.py` (~249 lines) - validator / logger for the
  4-phase query plan described in `references/query-plan.md`.
- `scripts/download_arxiv.py` (~79 lines) - batch PDF downloader that
  parses the Atom XML returned by arXiv and respects the 3 s throttle.
- `scripts/journal_lookup.py` (~141 lines) - reads `data/jcr.db` and
  returns JCR / CAS zone / impact factor for a given journal name or
  ISSN, used by `build_refs.py` when materialising `summary.md`.
- `scripts/wos_oa_download.py` (~95 lines) - queries Unpaywall per DOI
  and downloads the open-access PDF when available.
- `.gitignore` additions: `__pycache__/`, `*.pyc`, `.env`, `.env.*`,
  `config.local.md`, `paper_raw/`.

